Rao Satellite Centre in Bengaluru. The test was conducted between January 31 and February 2 and all the tests, including launcher compatibility, antenna polarization, standalone auto compatibility tests for orbital, powered descent mission phases, landerrover compatibility tests for postlanding mission, were satisfactory. This is a major boost to India's moon mission.
